card0.name: Pikachu
card0.description: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

card1.name: Charizard
card1.description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

card2.name: Bulbasaur
card2.description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

card3.name: Squirtle
card3.description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

card4.name: Caterpie
card4.description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

card5.name: Weedle
card5.description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

card6.name: Pidgey
card6.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

card7.name: Rattata
card7.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

card8.name: Spearow
card8.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

card9.name: Ekans
card9.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

65a55e0f891db.name: Charmander
65a55e0f891db.description: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

65a56506b9a62.name: Geodude
65a56506b9a62.description: Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

65a5e1e77cea2.name: Lopunny
65a5e1e77cea2.description: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.

65a5e272e7845.name: Bidoof
65a5e272e7845.description: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

65a5e2d586889.name: Burmy
65a5e2d586889.description: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

65a5e329391b9.name: Foongus
65a5e329391b9.description: There is a theory that the developer of the modern-day Poké Ball really liked Foongus, but this has not been confirmed.

65a6bbd366824.name: Muk
65a6bbd366824.description: It’s thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
